# AppPinManager 

The **AppPinManager** is a class used to add the application shortcut in StartMenu or TaskBar.It has following APIs

1.Task<PinResult> CurrentAppToTaskBarAsync()
Pin the current app shortcut in Windows10 TaskBar
Example 
var result = await AppPinManager.CurrentAppToTaskBarAsync();

2.Task<PinResult> SpecificAppToTaskBarAsync(AppListEntry appListEntry)
Pin the specified app shortcut in Windows10 TaskBar
Example 
var appList = (await Package.Current.GetAppListEntriesAsync())[0];
var result = await AppPinManager.SpecificAppToTaskBarAsync(appList);


3.Task<PinResult> SpecificAppToStartMenuAsync(AppListEntry entry)
Pin the specified app shortcut in Windows10 StartMenu
Example
var appList = (await Package.Current.GetAppListEntriesAsync())[0];
var result = await AppPinManager.SpecificAppToStartMenuAsync(appList);

4.Task<PinResult> UserSpecificAppToStartMenuAsync(User user, AppListEntry entry)
Pin the specified app shortcut in Windows10 StartMenu based on the user 
Example
var appList = (await Package.Current.GetAppListEntriesAsync())[0];
var result = await AppPinManager.UserSpecificAppToStartMenuAsync(user,appList);
Note : user , you have to pass the User object

All the APIs return the PinResult as a status
public enum PinResult
{
        UnsupportedDevice = 0,
        UnsupportedOs = 1,
        PinNotAllowed = 2,
        PinPresent = 3,
        PinAlreadyPresent = 4
}
